&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Simple query wizard&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To create a query object in Microsoft Access, you would use the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Simple Query Wizard.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Simple Query Wizard is a tool within Microsoft Access that assists users in creating custom queries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This tool guides users step-by-step in specifying the nature of the query, the data fields involved, and the output.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;With the Simple Query Wizard, users can construct basic queries such as &lt;strong&gt;Select, Parameter, Crosstab, Append, or Delete queries.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example, a &amp;quot;Select&amp;quot; query allows the user to select specific fields from one or more tables or queries, and retrieve records that meet certain criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Using the Simple Query Wizard is generally a straightforward process:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;First, you go to the &amp;quot;Create&amp;quot; tab on the toolbar, select &amp;quot;Query Wizard&amp;quot;, then choose &amp;quot;Simple Query Wizard&amp;quot; from the dialog box.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Next, you select the required tables or queries and the required fields for your new query.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Finally, you choose a detail (shows every field of every record) or summary (shows grouped data, like averages, counts, or sums) option, name your query, and then finish to create your new query based on your selections.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The &amp;quot;Database Wizard&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Simple Filter Wizard&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;Table Query Wizard&amp;quot; are not valid tools within MS Access for creating a query object.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Font Size&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Font Size&lt;/strong&gt; is a command used to change the size of the text in a document or application.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It allows users to adjust text visibility and readability according to their preferences or requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In most text editors or word processing software, the font size can be modified from a dropdown menu or a toolbar option.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Font size is typically measured in points (pt), with common values ranging from small sizes like 8pt to larger sizes like 72pt or more.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adjusting font size is a fundamental feature in designing documents, presentations, or any text-based content to ensure aesthetic appeal and proper formatting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications of Font Size Command:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Word Processing Software:&lt;/strong&gt; Enables users to format text for documents, resumes, reports, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Presentation Tools:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to highlight key points and ensure text visibility in slides.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Web Design:&lt;/strong&gt; Helps in creating responsive websites with readable text across various screen sizes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graphic Design:&lt;/strong&gt; Essential for typographical elements in posters, banners, and other creative content.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Font Size Options:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Small Font Sizes:&lt;/strong&gt; Ideal for footnotes, disclaimers, or compact designs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medium Font Sizes:&lt;/strong&gt; Commonly used for body text in documents and articles.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Large Font Sizes:&lt;/strong&gt; Suitable for headings, titles, or emphasis in presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advantages of Font Size Adjustment:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Improves text readability and enhances user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Allows customization to suit specific design or formatting needs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Helps in organizing content hierarchically for better understanding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important Points:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Font size should be chosen based on the context and audience for optimal readability.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overuse of large or small font sizes may impact the overall design quality.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Consistency in font size across a document ensures a professional appearance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disk Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disk Management&lt;/strong&gt; is a built-in Windows utility that allows users to manage their computer&amp;#39;s disk partitions effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Using Disk Management, you can perform various functions such as creating, deleting, resizing, or formatting partitions on your hard drive.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It also allows you to assign or change drive letters, which helps in organizing and identifying different drives on your system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This tool is especially useful when setting up a new hard drive or modifying the existing storage configuration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Disk Management is accessible through the Control Panel or by right-clicking on &amp;quot;This PC&amp;quot; and selecting &amp;quot;Manage,&amp;quot; followed by navigating to the &amp;quot;Disk Management&amp;quot; section.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Functions of Disk Management:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create Partitions:&lt;/strong&gt; You can divide a hard drive into multiple logical drives to organize and store data efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format Drives:&lt;/strong&gt; Disk Management enables you to format a partition, making it ready for storing data.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Change Drive Letters:&lt;/strong&gt; Users can assign or modify drive letters to make drives easily identifiable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shrink or Extend Partitions:&lt;/strong&gt; It allows resizing of partitions to allocate space effectively across drives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tools Comparison:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Task Manager:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to monitor system performance and manage running applications and processes, not for partition management.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Control Panel:&lt;/strong&gt; Provides access to system settings but does not directly manage disk partitions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notepad:&lt;/strong&gt; A simple text editor, not related to disk or partition management.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Steps to Access Disk Management:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Press &lt;strong&gt;Win + X&lt;/strong&gt; and select &amp;quot;Disk Management&amp;quot; from the menu.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, search for &amp;quot;Disk Management&amp;quot; in the Start menu or run &amp;quot;diskmgmt.msc&amp;quot; via the Run dialog box.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important Notes:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Always back up your data before modifying partitions to avoid data loss.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Disk Management is suitable for basic storage management; for advanced features, third-party tools may be required.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ensure you have administrative privileges to perform disk management tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
